# Grilled Peach, Chickpea & Feta Salad with Basil Vinaigrette  

## Ingredients  
- 3 ripe peaches, halved & pitted  
- Olive oil, for brushing  
- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained & rinsed  
- 4 cups baby lettuce mix  
- 1 cup microgreens (radish preferred)  
- 3 oz feta cheese, crumbled  
- 1/3 cup pepitas, toasted  

## Dressing: [Basil Vinaigrette](dressings/basil-vinagarette.md) 

## Instructions  
1. Preheat grill or grill pan. Brush peach halves lightly with olive oil, grill cut-side down until charred (3â€“4 min), then slice.  
2. Blend basil, olive oil, vinegar, Dijon, honey, salt & pepper into a smooth vinaigrette.  
3. Toss lettuce, microgreens, and chickpeas with basil vinaigrette. Spread on a platter.  
4. Arrange grilled peach slices over greens, sprinkle with feta and pepitas. Serve at once.  
